{
  "analysis": "The foreground training command is still blocking the shell after multiple long waits, and the queued diagnostic commands have not executed. Because `tail -120` buffers output until pipeline exit, there is no visibility into progress. We need to interrupt once, inspect process/files/disk, then either verify an existing model or restart with a background log so progress is visible.",
  "plan": "Send Ctrl+C to interrupt the stuck foreground pipeline. Then run process, file, and disk diagnostics to see whether a model or intermediate fastText files exist. If a valid model exists, we will verify it next; otherwise we will restart training in the background with a log file.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "C-c",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ps aux | grep -E 'python3|run_train' | grep -v grep\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -lh /app/*.txt /app/*.bin 2>&1\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "df -h /app\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}
